    "created_at": "2017-02-03T23:37:22Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-02-03T23:38:17Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yeah, because the pathfinder tries to find a path from the current position to any cell within `nearEnough`.  Halving that means that there are only 1/4 as many valid end points, and the pathing is 4 times more likely to fail.\r\n\r\nThis is of course completely bogus, but is a consequence of our pathfinder design not being able to handle open-ended paths (\"move as close as possible to point X\")."
  },
